<br>
In moments he reaches the gates of Olympus and steps out of his chariot. The Seasons bow to him, immediatly opening to gates to the returning god. As he passes them the burst into a girlish fit of whispers and giggles.<br>
<br>
He walks into the main thrown room to see if anyone is up and about yet, as it is only the wee hour of the morning. His red toga is bold against the golden sun light, his lauren crown gold;that of the sun, also his sandels of gold. With a grin across his face he enters, hopping to see his sister. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uposeidonkofc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Poseidonkofc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/1/01 8:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Triumphant Arrival</span><hr size=1> ::The Great god of the Sea is riding his golden Chariot over the calm sea waves in the mediteranean. He looks up and shades his eyes from the sun with his right hand. He sees that Apollo has just returned to Olympus and muffles angrily to himself as he holds the reigns again with both hands.:: <br>
