t of Mt. Olympus, looking up to the sky.  He watched this &quot;triumphant&quot; return of the bright one, Apollo.  The minotaur heard the laughter below through the sky and merely shook his head.  When he was young, all this pomp and circumstance used to impress him.  But after thousands of years of hardship, that's all it was to him, &quot;pom&quot;.  Mojo then slowly began his hard hike up to the summit of Olympus. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uthegreatapollo.showPublicProfile?language=EN>The Great Apollo</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 7<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/2/01 4:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=33.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A new outlook.</span><hr size=1> Apollo waves over to Hypnos with a smile and a nod. He shakes his head jesturing to the sea, for he knew of Poseidon's dismay at his arrival, rolling his eyes. His gaze wanders around the throne room his eyes looking for his father.<br>
